 @param tokenId - the ID of the token to be burned.
Additional Overrides to avoid library conflicts

devdoc.details: An NFT representation of a property. This contract allows for minting property NFTs, updating their attributes, and querying based on certain attributes like launchpadID. It also provides role-based access control for various operations.

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `owner` enables `approved` to manage the `tokenId` token.

ApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: Emitted when `owner` enables or disables (`approved`) `operator` to manage all of its assets.

BatchMetadataUpdate(uint256,uint256).details: This event emits when the metadata of a range of tokens is changed. So that the third-party platforms such as NFT market could timely update the images and related attributes of the NFTs.

MetadataUpdate(uint256).details: This event emits when the metadata of a token is changed. So that the third-party platforms such as NFT market could timely update the images and related attributes of the NFT.

PropertyMinted(uint256,string,uint256,ui.details: Emitted when a new property NFT is minted.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `tokenId` token is transferred from `from` to `to`.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approves another address to manage the specified token. Overrides ERC721's approve function.

params.tokenId: - The ID of the token to be approved for management.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the balance (number of tokens) of the specified owner. Overrides ERC721's balanceOf function.

params.owner: - The address of the user to fetch the balance for.

returns._0: The number of tokens owned by the specified address.

burnTokenWithApproval(uint256).details: Allows burning of a token after user's approval.

params.tokenId: - the ID of the token to be burned.

constructor.details: Sets up the main admin role on contract deployment.

distributeRewards(uint256,uint256,addres.details: Distributes rewards to NFT holders based on their properties' participation in a specified launchpad. The rewards are distributed in USD token. The contract needs to be approved by the operator to spend the USDT before calling this function.

params.TokenAddress: The address of the ERC20 token contract. Emits a `Transfer` event for each reward distribution. Requirements: - The caller must have the `operator` role. - The contract must be approved by the operator to spend at least `amount` of USDT. - The total distributed amount should match the specified `amount`.
params.amount: The total amount of USD to be distributed among the NFT holders.
params.launchpadID: The ID of the launchpad for which rewards are to be distributed.

getProperty(uint256).details: Fetches the Property details for a specific token ID.

params.tokenId: - The ID of the token to fetch the Property details for.

returns._0: A Property struct containing details about the specified property.

getTokensByLaunchpadID(uint256).details: Fetches all tokens associated with a particular launchpadID.

params._launchpadID: - the ID of the launchpad to query.

returns._0: A list of token IDs associated with the provided launchpadID.

params.launchpadID: - id of the launchpad that sold the property.
params.propertyParticipation: - amount user partecipated in the property.
params.redeemFees: - fees that will be paid when redeem the profit from property selling.
params.sellFees: - fees from selling the NFT in the marketplace.
params.to: - the recipient address of the minted token.
params.totalEarned: - revenue generated by the NFT property over time.
params.totalPropertyRaised: - Total sell value of the property.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the owner of the specified token ID. Overrides ERC721's ownerOf function.

params.tokenId: - The ID of the token to fetch the owner for.

returns._0: The address of the owner of the specified token.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers the ownership of a token from one address to another. Overrides ERC721's safeTransferFrom function.

params.from: - The current owner of the token.
params.to: - The address to receive the token.
params.tokenId: - The ID of the token to be transferred.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers the ownership of a token from one address to another, with additional data. Overrides ERC721's safeTransferFrom function.

params._data: - Additional data to accompany the transfer.
params.from: - The current owner of the token.
params.to: - The address to receive the token.
params.tokenId: - The ID of the token to be transferred.

setMinter(address).details: Assigns a minter role to an address.

params._minter: Address to be assigned the minter role.

setOperator(address).details: Assigns an operator role to an address.

params._operator: Address to be assigned the operator role.

setRedeemer(address).details: Assigns a redeemer role to an address.

params._redeemer: Address to be assigned the redeemer role.

setTokenURI(uint256,string).details: Sets the URI for a given token ID. Overrides the ERC721URIStorage setTokenURI functionality.

params.tokenId: - the ID of the token to set the URI for.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns the URI associated with a specific token ID. Overrides ERC721's tokenURI functionality.

params.tokenId: - The ID of the token to fetch the URI for.

returns._0: A string representing the URI of the specified token.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers the ownership of a token from one address to another. Overrides ERC721's transferFrom function.

params.from: - The current owner of the token.
params.to: - The address to receive the token.
params.tokenId: - The ID of the token to be transferred.

updateBulkRedeemFees(uint256[],uint256).details: Updates the redeemFees attribute for a multiple tokenIds.

params._redeemFees: - the new value for redeemFees to be set.

updateBulkSellFees(uint256[],uint256).details: Updates the sellFees attribute for a multiple tokenIds.

params._sellFees: - the new value for sellFees to be set.

updateRedeemFees(uint256,uint256).details: Updates the redeemfees attribute for a single  tokenIds.

params._redeemFees: - the new value for redeemfees to be set.

updateSellFees(uint256,uint256).details: Updates the sellFees attribute for a single  tokenIds.

params._sellFees: - the new value for sellFees to be set.
